parameters.name: AddressFamily
parameters.description:
The IP address family. Valid values:

*   IPv4
*   IPv6

This parameter is empty by default, which indicates that all prefix lists are queried.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description:
The number of entries per page.

Valid values: 1 to 100.

Default value: 10.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description: The pagination token that is used in the request to retrieve a new page of results. Set the value to the `NextToken` value returned in the last call to this operation. Leave this parameter empty the first time you call this operation.

parameters.name: PrefixListId
parameters.description: The IDs of prefix lists. Valid values of N: 0 to 100.

parameters.name: PrefixListName
parameters.description: The name of the prefix list.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description: The region ID. You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~25609~~) operation to query the most recent region list.

parameters.name: ResourceGroupId
parameters.description: The ID of the resource group to which the prefix list belongs.

parameters.name: Tag
parameters.description: The tags of the prefix list.
